# Shared Modules

- Used by **both** server and browser — keep Node/browser compatible (no `fs`, no DOM)
- Export named constants and pure functions only
- Socket event names → [kernel/events.js](../../shared/kernel/events.js) (re-exported by [events.js](../../shared/events.js))
- Game constants (tiles, sizes, speeds) → [constants.js](../../shared/constants.js)
- Cross-cutting algorithms (pathfinding, combat formulas) → dedicated files, fully pure

When adding a constant used on both sides, add it here once — never duplicate in server and client.

## Layout

```
shared/
├── kernel/events.js      # canonical EVENTS
├── plugins/              # domain logic (combat/, core/anticheat, render/particles, world/delta+chunks)
├── audioSettings.js      # client audio prefs, music mood by map
├── uiThemeSettings.js    # client UI theme ids, localStorage, canvas palettes
├── worldMaps.js          # MAP_ID, zone display names
├── content/              # quests.json, skills.json, vendors.json
│   └── validateContent.js
└── *.js                  # top-level modules; some are re-export stubs (combat.js, events.js)
```

## Domain plugins (`shared/plugins/`)

- Pure game logic shared by server handlers and tests (e.g. `shared/plugins/combat/advancedCombat.js`)
- Plugin type contracts → `shared/plugins/types.js`
- Domain events for server bus → `shared/plugins/domainEvents.js`
- Do not put socket handlers or DOM code here

## Content packs (`shared/content/`)

- Static data as JSON; validated at server startup via `server/app/loadContent.js`
- Helpers that interpret content stay in JS modules (e.g. `shared/skills.js` imports `skills.json`)
- Update `validateContent.js` when adding required fields or new content files

## Testing

- Shared pure functions → `tests/shared/<module>.test.js` or `tests/shared/plugins/<domain>/`
- Critical gameplay coverage index → [tests/README.md](../../tests/README.md) (combat, loot, movement, anticheat)
- Keep tests deterministic; no DOM or Node-only APIs in shared code
